    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> &rsaquo; <a href="/library" class="active">Regis Library</a> &rsaquo; Regis College Library</div><h1>Regis College Library</h1><div id="node-10" class="node clear-block">



  <div class="content clear-block">
        <div><img alt="Regis Library" class="alignleft" src="/files/images/regis_library.jpg" style="width: 135px; float: left; height: 180px" /><strong>Welcome</strong><p>Regis College Library&nbsp;offers&nbsp; the advantages of a small local library and&nbsp;advantages of a large research university library system. Established in 1930 to serve the Jesuit Seminary, the library&nbsp;currently&nbsp; holds approximately 60,000 volumes and carries about 140 current journal subscriptions. The collection includes a wide variety of theological materials with emphases on Christian spirituality (with a specialization in the Spiritual Exercises of St. Ignatius); Christian ethics; Roman Catholic systematic and historical theology; classic Christian texts in their original languages and in translation.Our holdings can be searched through the University of Toronto Libraries <a href="http://onesearch.library.utoronto.ca/">Catalogue</a>. Our latest acquisitions are listed in <a href="http://www.regiscollege.ca/library/new_and_notable">New and Notable </a>.</p><p>Computer workstations and wireless internet access are available to all those whole hold a valid <a href="http://www.utoronto.ca/tcard/">T-card</a>. Library staff are available to answer your questions and provide research and reference assistance, just <a href="http://www.regiscollege.ca/library/reference">ask a librarian</a>. &nbsp;Our <a href="http://www.regiscollege.ca/ask">ASk</a> or Academic Skills Program provides workshops and consultations.</p>Telephone: 416-922-5474 x234</div><div>E-mail: <a href="mailto:regis.library@utoronto.ca">regis.library@utoronto.ca</a> / <a href="/info/library_contact">Contact Form</a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><p>&nbsp;</p>  </div>

